a)The most suitable Operating System for this environment is a Multi-user Operating System.
Justification:
A multi-user operating system allows more than one user to use the same computer at the same time.
  For example, in a university computer lab, many students can log in to the same Linux system and run their own programs. 
  The operating system manages the CPU, memory, and other resources so that each user can work properly without disturbing others.
  Linux is a good example of a multi-user operating system because it supports multiple users and gives each user a separate account with their own permissions.
b)TWO RESPONSIBILITY OF KERNEL IN MANAGING MULTI USER OPERATING SYSTEM
 the main two responsibility of kernel
 1.process schdeuling 
 2.memory management
 1. Process Scheduling:
The kernel decides which process should use the CPU and for how long.
  It switches between different processes so that all users can run their programs smoothly.
2. Memory Management:
The kernel allocates memory to each process and protects one process from accessing another process's memory. 
  This helps the system run safely and prevents data corruption.
