****question 4****
a) purpose of fork() and exec()_
1.fork()
The fork() system call is used to create a new child process.
The child process is a copy of the parent process.
2.exec()
The exec() system call is used to replace the current process with a new program.
After exec() is called, the new program starts executing.
b)Role of wait()
The wait() system call is used by the parent process to wait until the child process finishes its execution.
It helps the parent process continue only after the child process has completed its work.
